Getting Started

Welcome to query.gg, the official React Query course.

Before we dive in, here are some things to help you get the most out of the course.

First, this is an advanced course that assumes you have a fairly solid understanding of both JavaScript and React. If you don't, check out our other courses before diving into this one.

Second, the primary reason our courses take so long to create is because for every lesson, you're given both text and a video. They cover the same material, but they do so in slightly different ways in order to optimize for the different mediums.

We recommend you start with the text first, and then watch the video second. This may seem counterproductive, but having the ability to go through both is consistently the biggest source of praise we get, and it really helps the topics to "click".

Third, I know it's tempting, but don't skip the quizzes and challenges. This isn't school and you're not being graded. The only goal is to help you get a first principles understanding of React Query so that you can use it in your job. The only way you'll do that is by putting into practice what you learn in the lesson.

Finally, if you get stuck at any point, don't hesitate to create a new thread or hop onto an existing one. We're here to help you succeed and we'll do everything we can to make sure you do.

This course wasn't cheap, and the opportunity cost of your time going through it is even more expensive. We don't take that for granted and we hope it lives up to the bar we've set for ourselves.

Good luck.

- Tyler, Dominik, Lynn, and Ben
